{
  "texts": [
    "Cryptography refers to the science of secure communications, namely ways to ensure communications remain confidential, authentic, tamper-resistant, and only comprehensible by intended participants.",
    "It is used for securing various types of information and permeates several facets of everyday life, from sending encrypted text messages to online banking.",
    "Zero-shot transfer means that the LLM has neither been given relevant examples in the prompt, nor further fine-tuned (i.e., trained on many examples to produce a model which will accept either zero-shot or multi-shot prompts).",
    "However, because large-scale pre-trained models could happen to incorporate some relevant examples in their training data, this is distinct from zero-shot learning (Allingham et al. 2023).",
    "We chose 0.2 instead of 0 because, while we wanted a highly deterministic output, we wanted some randomness to allow for some variability in our output."
  ]
}